cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC 

This paper is primarily focused on the security aspect of bug bounty programs, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). However, the paper also touches upon software development roles and motivations, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the analysis of bug bounty program histories and contributors could involve aspects of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the survey conducted in the paper could be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
